  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project & Site Manager (Interior Design & Renovation)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Oversee the full project cycle from start to handover ensuring timely completion, high quality standards and client satisfaction.</li><li>Plan project schedules, manage timelines, budgets, documentation and ensure projects stay within scope and cost.</li><li>Conduct regular site inspections to monitor progress, workmanship, quality control, and resolve site issues promptly.</li><li>Act as the primary point of contact for clients, providing timely updates and responses to queries.</li><li>Coordinate closely with designers, subcontractors, suppliers, and internal teams on design intent, materials, schedules, and workflow.</li><li>Manage and supervise subcontractors; ensure clear scope of work and adherence to project requirements.</li><li>Attend site meetings and liaise with relevant stakeholders to ensure smooth project execution.</li><li>Review and interpret 2D drawings, technical specifications and assist in material selection and costing/negotiations with suppliers and subcontractors.</li><li>Support the preparation of quotations, work schedules, material / moodboards and other project-related documents when required.</li><li>Assist Sales Designers in the interior design scope.</li><li>Provide regular updates to internal stakeholders and escalate critical issues when necessary.</li><li>Participate in ad-hoc tasks or additional duties as assigned.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Proven experience in managing interior design, renovation, or construction projects.</li><li>Strong knowledge of Singapore's interior construction processes, materials, and vendor / subcontractor management.</li><li>Ability to multitask and manage multiple ongoing projects under tight deadlines.</li><li>Strong project coordination, site management and problem-solving skills.</li><li>Detail-oriented, proactive, and able to work independently as well as collaboratively.</li><li>Good interpersonal and communication skills to liaise with clients, subcontractors, and internal teams.</li><li>Proficiency in English; Mandarin is an advantage (for liaising with directors, clients, and contractors).</li><li>Possession of a personal vehicle is an added advantage.</li></ul><p>Interested candidates, please WhatsApp us at https://wa.me/6581170774 or email us at reborninteriorsg@gmail.com. We will only notify you if you are shortlisted. Thank you.</p>",
